      Emoji contract
   =20
 =20

I mean  sure, of course, thumbs up:

Be careful before you casually dash off another thumbs-up emoji: A Canadian=
 court has found that the ubiquitous symbol can affirm that a person is off=
icially entering into a contract.
The ruling pointed to what a judge called the =E2=80=9Cnew reality in Canad=
ian society=E2=80=9D that courts would have to confront as more people expr=
ess themselves with hearts, smiley faces and fire emojis =E2=80=94 even in =
serious business dealings or personal disputes.
The case questioned whether a farmer in Saskatchewan had agreed to sell 87 =
metric tons of flax to a grain buyer in 2021. The buyer had signed the cont=
ract and texted a photo of it to the farmer, who had responded by texting b=
ack a =E2=80=9Cthumbs-up=E2=80=9D emoji. =E2=80=A6
The judge noted that Mr. Achter and Mr. Mickleborough had had a longstandin=
g business relationship and that, in the past, when Mr. Mr. Mickleborough h=
ad texted Mr. Achter contracts for durum wheat, Mr. Achter had responded by=
 succinctly texting =E2=80=9Clooks good,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cok=E2=80=9D or =
=E2=80=9Cyup.=E2=80=9D
Both parties clearly understood these terse responses were meant to be conf=
irmation of the contract and =E2=80=9Cnot a mere acknowledgment of the rece=
ipt of the contract=E2=80=9D by Mr. Achter, wrote Justice T.J. Keene of the=
 Court of King=E2=80=99s Bench for Saskatchewan. And each time, Mr. Achter =
had delivered the grain as contracted and had been paid.

Is that even interesting? A lot of trading in financial markets is done by =
chat messages, and it is pretty clear that if you type =E2=80=9Cdone=E2=80=
=9D in a chat message that can create a binding contract. The difference be=
tween =E2=80=9Cdone=E2=80=9D and the thumbs-up emoji is not that great, and=
 I suspect it=E2=80=99s mostly generational; the emoji seems like a perfect=
ly reasonable way to say =E2=80=9Cyes I agree to these terms for our trade.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0In a few years the eggplant emoji will be the normal way to =
bind banks to nine-digit swaps trades.

