, so they don=E2=80=99t want to spend the buyer=E2=80=99s money=C2=A0<em>to=
o=C2=A0</em>aggressively. (Unless they are pretty sure that they <em>won=E2=
=80=99t </em>remain employed, in which case, who cares!) But these are pret=
ty soft constraints.</p>
