f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5703453b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> sure, of course</a>, thumbs up:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Be careful before you casually dash off anothe=
r thumbs-up emoji: A Canadian court has found that the ubiquitous symbol ca=
n affirm that a person is officially entering into a contract.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The ruling pointed to what a judge called the =
=E2=80=9Cnew reality in Canadian society=E2=80=9D that courts would have to=
 confront as more people express themselves with hearts, smiley faces and f=
ire emojis =E2=80=94 even in serious business dealings or personal disputes=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The case questioned whether a farmer in Saskat=
chewan had agreed to sell 87 metric tons of flax to a grain buyer in 2021. =
The buyer had signed the contract and texted a photo of it to the farmer, w=
ho had responded by texting back a =E2=80=9Cthumbs-up=E2=80=9D emoji. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The judge noted that Mr. Achter and Mr. Mickle=
borough had had a longstanding business relationship and that, in the past,=
 when Mr. Mr. Mickleborough had texted Mr. Achter contracts for durum wheat=
, Mr. Achter had responded by succinctly texting =E2=80=9Clooks good,=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=9Cok=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cyup.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both parties clearly understood these terse re=
sponses were meant to be confirmation of the contract and =E2=80=9Cnot a me=
re acknowledgment of the receipt of the contract=E2=80=9D by Mr. Achter, wr=
ote Justice T.J. Keene of the Court of King=E2=80=99s Bench for Saskatchewa=
n. And each time, Mr. Achter had delivered the grain as contracted and had =
been paid.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is that even interesting? A lot of trading in =
financial markets is done by chat messages, and it is pretty clear that if =
you type =E2=80=9Cdone=E2=80=9D in a chat message that can create a binding=
 contract. The difference between =E2=80=9Cdone=E2=80=9D and the thumbs-up =
emoji is not that great, and I suspect it=E2=80=99s mostly generational; th=
e emoji seems like a perfectly reasonable way to say =E2=80=9Cyes I agree t=
o these terms for our trade.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0In a few years the eggplant emoj=
i will be the normal way to bind banks to nine-digit swaps trades.</p>
